1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper focuses on learning activity recognition models from temporally sparse data using deep learning paradigm in an end-to-end manner. 
2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the use of passive wearables for healthcare applications for older people, which falls under the domain of human-computer interaction. 
3. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the use of passive wearables for healthcare applications, which has societal implications. 
4. cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper deals with processing sensor data streams for human activity recognition. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses set-based neural networks for activity recognition, which falls under the domain of neural computing.
